00:38:00.020 --> 00:38:01.240 align:middle line:10%
>> We got right up to it.

00:38:01.240 --> 00:38:02.260 align:middle line:10%
It lit up.

00:38:02.260 --> 00:38:03.640 align:middle line:10%
I mean, it really become bright.

00:38:03.640 --> 00:38:07.990 align:middle line:10%
And we could see it, the
outline of it, real good.

00:38:07.990 --> 00:38:11.500 align:middle line:10%
>> Blue Book's Doctor Allen
Hynek investigated one

00:38:11.500 --> 00:38:15.850 align:middle line:10%
of the alleged landing sites
with the local sheriff.

00:38:15.850 --> 00:38:20.350 align:middle line:10%
At an overflow press conference
later that day, the world

00:38:20.350 --> 00:38:24.640 align:middle line:10%
held its breath for an historic
revelation about the landings

00:38:24.640 --> 00:38:26.200 align:middle line:10%
in Michigan.

00:38:26.200 --> 00:38:30.910 align:middle line:10%
Hynek, by now privately
convinced of the UFO reality,

00:38:30.910 --> 00:38:35.530 align:middle line:10%
struggled to follow the Air
Force policy of tamping down

00:38:35.530 --> 00:38:37.712 align:middle line:10%
public excitement.

00:38:37.712 --> 00:38:39.920 align:middle line:10%
>> Are you saying that the
sightings in the Ann Arbor

00:38:39.920 --> 00:38:43.850 align:middle line:10%
and Hillsdale areas definitely
were caused by marsh gases?

00:38:43.850 --> 00:38:47.780 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm saying that the two cases
that I investigated most deeply

00:38:47.780 --> 00:38:49.493 align:middle line:90%
were most likely.

00:38:49.493 --> 00:38:51.410 align:middle line:10%
I said in a statement
that I couldn't prove it

00:38:51.410 --> 00:38:52.785 align:middle line:10%
in a court of law,
but it seems--

00:38:52.785 --> 00:38:55.368 align:middle line:10%
>> In other words, you're saying
then that you don't know what

00:38:55.368 --> 00:38:56.390 align:middle line:10%
caused it.

00:38:56.390 --> 00:38:57.950 align:middle line:90%
>> No, that's not quite right.

00:38:57.950 --> 00:39:01.430 align:middle line:84%
I think that a person can be
pretty sure about something

00:39:01.430 --> 00:39:04.107 align:middle line:84%
without being able to
convict somebody of a murder.

00:39:04.107 --> 00:39:04.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Can you believe--

00:39:04.940 --> 00:39:05.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Can you say--

00:39:05.740 --> 00:39:10.058 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, I do honestly in
this case, in this case.

00:39:10.058 --> 00:39:12.350 align:middle line:10%
>> But you can't say without
question that this is what

00:39:12.350 --> 00:39:13.150 align:middle line:10%
caused it?

00:39:13.150 --> 00:39:17.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Hynek's strained explanation,
which he later called his

00:39:17.210 --> 00:39:20.660 align:middle line:84%
greatest regret,
ignited a public furor.

00:39:20.660 --> 00:39:23.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Mr. Ford, what
about flying saucers?

00:39:23.480 --> 00:39:26.270 align:middle line:84%
You've had some in
Michigan in the past week.

00:39:26.270 --> 00:39:32.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Dave, we've had several
incidents that many felt were

00:39:32.060 --> 00:39:36.080 align:middle line:84%
sufficient to justify some
action by our government

00:39:36.080 --> 00:39:39.410 align:middle line:84%
and not the kind of flippant
answer that was given

00:39:39.410 --> 00:39:44.960 align:middle line:84%
by the Air Force, where they
passed it off as swamp gas.

00:39:44.960 --> 00:39:48.770 align:middle line:84%
It seems to me that
this mystery does

00:39:48.770 --> 00:39:52.310 align:middle line:84%
require that the Congress
take a good look at it.

00:39:52.310 --> 00:39:56.350 align:middle line:84%
Let them put their
record on the line.

00:39:56.350 --> 00:40:00.370 align:middle line:84%
>> On April 5, 1966,
congressional hearings were

00:40:00.370 --> 00:40:03.940 align:middle line:84%
held with Dr. Hynek and
Secretary of the Air Force

00:40:03.940 --> 00:40:06.910 align:middle line:84%
Harold Brown both
giving testimony.

00:40:06.910 --> 00:40:09.990 align:middle line:90%


00:40:09.990 --> 00:40:12.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Mr. Ford has come out.

00:40:12.070 --> 00:40:15.420 align:middle line:84%
He has a pretty good sized
stature in the Congress.

00:40:15.420 --> 00:40:19.290 align:middle line:84%
And so Mr. Secretary,
see if you can

00:40:19.290 --> 00:40:24.780 align:middle line:84%
shed some light on these
highly illuminated objects.

00:40:24.780 --> 00:40:27.390 align:middle line:84%
>> Mr. Secretary, there have
been charges that the Air Force

00:40:27.390 --> 00:40:29.850 align:middle line:84%
is hiding something
in the UFO field.

00:40:29.850 --> 00:40:32.910 align:middle line:10%
>> We have not been
hiding anything.

00:40:32.910 --> 00:40:36.480 align:middle line:10%
The investigations
have been made public.

00:40:36.480 --> 00:40:39.450 align:middle line:10%
The hearing this morning was
public for just that reason.

00:40:39.450 --> 00:40:42.180 align:middle line:10%
>> There has never been
any evidence presented

00:40:42.180 --> 00:40:45.840 align:middle line:10%
to the United States Air Force
or discovered by the United

00:40:45.840 --> 00:40:48.960 align:middle line:10%
States Air Force which
would indicate that the UFO

00:40:48.960 --> 00:40:53.310 align:middle line:10%
phenomenon represents any
interplanetary space vehicle

00:40:53.310 --> 00:40:54.120 align:middle line:10%
of any kind.

00:40:54.120 --> 00:40:57.300 align:middle line:90%


00:40:57.300 --> 00:40:59.850 align:middle line:10%
>> Amid growing pressure,
the Air Force commissioned

00:40:59.850 --> 00:41:04.410 align:middle line:10%
an outside panel of scientists
to analyze select cases

00:41:04.410 --> 00:41:07.780 align:middle line:10%
and settle the matter
once and for all.

00:41:07.780 --> 00:41:11.080 align:middle line:84%
It was headed by
physicist Edward Condon.

00:41:11.080 --> 00:41:14.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Dr. Condon, do you hope to
find people from outer space

00:41:14.890 --> 00:41:16.270 align:middle line:90%
here on Earth?

00:41:16.270 --> 00:41:19.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I don't know for sure,
but we'll try to just study

00:41:19.540 --> 00:41:22.480 align:middle line:84%
the reports and get as much
additional information as we

00:41:22.480 --> 00:41:23.920 align:middle line:90%
can to see.

00:41:23.920 --> 00:41:27.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Would you like to have us
being visited by these little

00:41:27.460 --> 00:41:28.750 align:middle line:90%
or big things?

00:41:28.750 --> 00:41:32.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that would be fine with
me if I hope they're friendly.

00:41:32.320 --> 00:41:34.090 align:middle line:10%
>> How do you
propose to go about--

00:41:34.090 --> 00:41:35.890 align:middle line:10%
>> After the project
was launched,

00:41:35.890 --> 00:41:39.760 align:middle line:10%
Condon remarked to an audience
that he thought the UFO subject

00:41:39.760 --> 00:41:44.200 align:middle line:10%
was nonsense, but, quote, "I'm
not supposed to reach that

00:41:44.200 --> 00:41:46.030 align:middle line:10%
conclusion for another year."

00:41:46.030 --> 00:41:49.850 align:middle line:90%


00:41:49.850 --> 00:41:54.020 align:middle line:84%
After a two-year investigation,
the panel submitted a massive

00:41:54.020 --> 00:41:58.940 align:middle line:84%
1,400-page report, showing
that many cases were radar

00:41:58.940 --> 00:42:03.170 align:middle line:84%
and weather anomalies, but
confirming a number as truly

00:42:03.170 --> 00:42:05.210 align:middle line:90%
unexplainable.

00:42:05.210 --> 00:42:08.510 align:middle line:10%
Among them were the famous
McMinnville photos taken

00:42:08.510 --> 00:42:11.900 align:middle line:10%
on the Trent family
farm, as well as

00:42:11.900 --> 00:42:17.070 align:middle line:10%
film footage of refers
in Great Falls, Montana.

00:42:17.070 --> 00:42:20.730 align:middle line:84%
>> As I looked up, I saw two
silvery objects moving swiftly

00:42:20.730 --> 00:42:21.900 align:middle line:90%
out of the northwest.

00:42:21.900 --> 00:42:24.330 align:middle line:84%
No sound, except I thought
I heard a whooshing

00:42:24.330 --> 00:42:26.220 align:middle line:90%
sound when I first saw them.

00:42:26.220 --> 00:42:28.770 align:middle line:84%
