and it is fantastic.

00:46:01.650 --> 00:46:05.010 align:middle line:10%
In 1967, I was a
missile launch officer

00:46:05.010 --> 00:46:07.740 align:middle line:10%
stationed at Malmstrom
Air Force Base Montana.

00:46:07.740 --> 00:46:12.420 align:middle line:10%
>> Malmstrom was America's
first line of nuclear defense.

00:46:12.420 --> 00:46:17.700 align:middle line:84%
Its silos packed with Minuteman
missiles, each one nearly 100

00:46:17.700 --> 00:46:23.200 align:middle line:84%
times more powerful than the
bomb that devastated Hiroshima.

00:46:23.200 --> 00:46:26.890 align:middle line:84%
Launch officers could, within
minutes of confirmation,

00:46:26.890 --> 00:46:30.310 align:middle line:84%
send their birds
arcing 6,000 miles

00:46:30.310 --> 00:46:35.560 align:middle line:84%
to incinerate key Soviet
cities, triggering a war that

00:46:35.560 --> 00:46:37.540 align:middle line:90%
would end our civilization.

00:46:37.540 --> 00:46:51.673 align:middle line:90%


00:46:51.673 --> 00:46:52.840 align:middle line:10%
>> I was the chief of party.

00:46:52.840 --> 00:46:54.280 align:middle line:10%
I was the observer.

00:46:54.280 --> 00:46:56.950 align:middle line:10%
Basically, what I was doing
was the star observation

00:46:56.950 --> 00:47:00.430 align:middle line:10%
to provide precise
latitude and longitude

00:47:00.430 --> 00:47:03.250 align:middle line:10%
on our small three-man team.

00:47:03.250 --> 00:47:07.120 align:middle line:84%
Came from the north and
stopped right over us.

00:47:07.120 --> 00:47:11.710 align:middle line:84%
And it had a white light
from the center looking down

00:47:11.710 --> 00:47:13.270 align:middle line:90%
into the silo.

00:47:13.270 --> 00:47:15.790 align:middle line:84%
I just said to myself,
what if this thing beams us

00:47:15.790 --> 00:47:18.370 align:middle line:84%
up and takes us off
to some distant place

00:47:18.370 --> 00:47:19.930 align:middle line:84%
and never returned
to Earth again?

00:47:19.930 --> 00:47:21.472 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is
going through my head

00:47:21.472 --> 00:47:23.560 align:middle line:84%
here while this
thing's above me.

00:47:23.560 --> 00:47:28.373 align:middle line:84%
And then from this dead stop,
it shoots off to the east,

00:47:28.373 --> 00:47:30.040 align:middle line:84%
just like now you see
it, now you don't.

00:47:30.040 --> 00:47:30.840 align:middle line:90%
It just--

00:47:30.840 --> 00:47:34.658 align:middle line:90%


00:47:34.658 --> 00:47:36.950 align:middle line:84%
>> This flight team that went
out claimed that they saw

00:47:36.950 --> 00:47:37.400 align:middle line:90%
something.

00:47:37.400 --> 00:47:38.650 align:middle line:10%
>> How did they describe that?

00:47:38.650 --> 00:47:40.220 align:middle line:10%
>> He just said a
large round object.

00:47:40.220 --> 00:47:41.360 align:middle line:10%
>> Directly over the LS?

00:47:41.360 --> 00:47:42.443 align:middle line:90%
>> Directly over the site.

00:47:42.443 --> 00:47:49.290 align:middle line:90%


00:47:49.290 --> 00:47:52.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Lieutenant Salas was
stationed in his underground

00:47:52.050 --> 00:47:56.310 align:middle line:84%
launch control capsule when he
received a frantic call from

00:47:56.310 --> 00:47:58.350 align:middle line:90%
one of his topside guards.

00:47:58.350 --> 00:48:02.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Screaming into the phone
saying they're looking a red

00:48:02.040 --> 00:48:06.030 align:middle line:84%
glowing object hovering
just above our front gate.

00:48:06.030 --> 00:48:09.690 align:middle line:84%
Our missiles began going into
what's called a no-go condition

00:48:09.690 --> 00:48:11.790 align:middle line:90%
