00:48:20.230 --> 00:48:22.930 align:middle line:90%
of seconds, one after the other.

00:48:22.930 --> 00:48:26.508 align:middle line:90%


00:48:26.508 --> 00:48:29.050 align:middle line:10%
>> Personally, I'm never aware
of any two missiles going down

00:48:29.050 --> 00:48:31.090 align:middle line:10%
at the same time, let alone 10.

00:48:31.090 --> 00:48:32.890 align:middle line:10%
>> I was a top secret
control officer,

00:48:32.890 --> 00:48:36.430 align:middle line:10%
and I passed out nuclear
launch authenticators.

00:48:36.430 --> 00:48:38.380 align:middle line:84%
I can clearly recall
a message coming

00:48:38.380 --> 00:48:41.200 align:middle line:84%
through my communications
center which basically

00:48:41.200 --> 00:48:45.550 align:middle line:84%
said that a UFO did in fact
shut down several missile

00:48:45.550 --> 00:48:46.960 align:middle line:90%
silos in Montana.

00:48:46.960 --> 00:48:53.550 align:middle line:90%


00:48:53.550 --> 00:48:56.640 align:middle line:10%
>> I was on duty at Echo, which
our squadron command post.

00:48:56.640 --> 00:49:00.420 align:middle line:10%
We had strike teams respond
to alarms from the missiles.

00:49:00.420 --> 00:49:02.140 align:middle line:10%
They were three to
five miles away.

00:49:02.140 --> 00:49:04.770 align:middle line:84%
And they said, Sir, lack
of a better description,

00:49:04.770 --> 00:49:07.110 align:middle line:84%
there's a flying saucer
hovering over that missile.

00:49:07.110 --> 00:49:11.790 align:middle line:84%
And there's a beam of reddish
light going down to it.

00:49:11.790 --> 00:49:13.620 align:middle line:84%
It had to be a data
collection thing.

00:49:13.620 --> 00:49:15.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure they scanned
the warhead or something.

00:49:15.730 --> 00:49:20.640 align:middle line:90%


00:49:20.640 --> 00:49:23.700 align:middle line:10%
>> In 1980, I was reassigned
from the Pentagon to RAF

00:49:23.700 --> 00:49:25.980 align:middle line:10%
Bentwaters as a
deputy base commander.

00:49:25.980 --> 00:49:28.710 align:middle line:84%
At that time, Bentwaters was one
of the largest tactical fighter

00:49:28.710 --> 00:49:30.820 align:middle line:90%
ranges in the world.

00:49:30.820 --> 00:49:34.590 align:middle line:84%
>> It was also the largest
American nuclear bomb storage

00:49:34.590 --> 00:49:36.510 align:middle line:90%
depot in Europe.

00:49:36.510 --> 00:49:39.090 align:middle line:84%
>> In December 1980,
early in the morning,

00:49:39.090 --> 00:49:41.760 align:middle line:84%
several of our security
policemen discovered strange

00:49:41.760 --> 00:49:43.140 align:middle line:90%
lights in the forest.

00:49:43.140 --> 00:49:45.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Expecting to find
a crashed aircraft,

00:49:45.450 --> 00:49:50.070 align:middle line:84%
they came upon an unrecognizable
object resting on the forest

00:49:50.070 --> 00:49:51.540 align:middle line:90%
floor.

00:49:51.540 --> 00:49:53.800 align:middle line:84%
>> They observed it
for a period of time.

00:49:53.800 --> 00:49:56.700 align:middle line:84%
And it very quickly
and silently vanished.

00:49:56.700 --> 00:50:01.590 align:middle line:90%


00:50:01.590 --> 00:50:05.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Two nights later, Colonel
Halt received an urgent visit

00:50:05.220 --> 00:50:08.100 align:middle line:84%
from the base
security commander.

00:50:08.100 --> 00:50:09.900 align:middle line:90%
>> He was white as a sheet.

00:50:09.900 --> 00:50:11.700 align:middle line:90%
He said, it's back.

00:50:11.700 --> 00:50:12.870 align:middle line:10%
I said, what's back?

00:50:12.870 --> 00:50:16.020 align:middle line:90%
He said, the UFO.

00:50:16.020 --> 00:50:18.130 align:middle line:84%
I took several security
policemen with me.

00:50:18.130 --> 00:50:20.940 align:middle line:84%
I also had my small cassette
recorder I carried everywhere

00:50:20.940 --> 00:50:22.310 align:middle line:90%
when I was on duty.

00:50:22.310 --> 00:50:23.110 align:middle line:90%
>> What is it?

00:50:23.110 --> 00:50:24.362 align:middle line:90%
>> We don't know, sir.

00:50:24.362 --> 00:50:25.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Can I get some [INAUDIBLE]

00:50:25.570 --> 00:50:28.205 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, it's a strange
small red light.

00:50:28.205 --> 00:50:29.580 align:middle line:84%
And all the barnyard
animals have

00:50:29.580 --> 00:50:32.340 align:middle line:90%
gotten quiet now, deathly calm.

00:50:32.340 --> 00:50:33.360 align:middle line:90%
This is weird.

00:50:33.360 --> 00:50:36.270 align:middle line:90%


00:50:36.270 --> 00:50:38.837 align:middle line:84%
>> One object approached
us at very high speed.

00:50:38.837 --> 00:50:40.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Here he comes from the south.

00:50:40.170 --> 00:50:41.585 align:middle line:90%
He's coming toward us now.

00:50:41.585 --> 00:50:42.960 align:middle line:84%
Now, we're observing
what appears

00:50:42.960 --> 00:50:46.262 align:middle line:84%
to be a beam coming
down to the ground.

00:50:46.262 --> 00:50:48.300 align:middle line:90%
This is unreal.

00:50:48.300 --> 00:50:50.300 align:middle line:90%
>> We stood there in awe.

00:50:50.300 --> 00:50:51.660 align:middle line:90%
Was this just a warning?

00:50:51.660 --> 00:50:53.940 align:middle line:84%
Was this an attempt
to communicate?

00:50:53.940 --> 00:50:57.060 align:middle line:84%
Was this a weapon
or just a probe?

00:50:57.060 --> 00:51:01.330 align:middle line:84%
Just as suddenly as it
appeared, click, disappeared.

00:51:01.330 --> 00:51:04.480 align:middle line:90%
We stood there, ah.

00:51:04.480 --> 00:51:06.910 align:middle line:84%
About that time, we noticed
the other object to the south

00:51:06.910 --> 00:51:09.490 align:middle line:84%
was sending down beams,
about a mile and a half

00:51:09.490 --> 00:51:12.340 align:middle line:84%
away over Woodbridge Base,
when we had great difficulties

00:51:12.340 --> 00:51:13.300 align:middle line:90%
communicating.

00:51:13.300 --> 00:51:15.550 align:middle line:84%
But we were able to
discern some of those beams

00:51:15.550 --> 00:51:18.220 align:middle line:84%
were either falling into or
near the weapons storage area,

00:51:18.220 --> 00:51:20.740 align:middle line:84%
and there's a great
deal of concern.

00:51:20.740 --> 00:51:23.290 align:middle line:84%
I also found out later
that both the tower

00:51:23.290 --> 00:51:26.230 align:middle line:84%
operators at Bentwaters
saw an object

00:51:26.230 --> 00:51:29.510 align:middle line:84%
and picked it up on their
Brite II radar and watched it.

00:51:29.510 --> 00:51:33.160 align:middle line:10%
>> I was just sitting there,
and I happened to see a dot come

00:51:33.160 --> 00:51:34.300 align:middle line:10%
on the scope.

00:51:34.300 --> 00:51:37.510 align:middle line:10%
And it just went like
one dot of beginning,

00:51:37.510 --> 00:51:40.130 align:middle line:10%
then another dot, and
another dot, and it was gone.

00:51:40.130 --> 00:51:42.430 align:middle line:84%
And then it made a
immediate right-hand turn

00:51:42.430 --> 00:51:44.050 align:middle line:90%
and came right towards the base.

00:51:44.050 --> 00:51:46.190 align:middle line:90%
Just absolutely phenomenal.

00:51:46.190 --> 00:51:50.050 align:middle line:10%
>> It's not like any radar
target I've ever seen traveling

00:51:50.050 --> 00:51:52.690 align:middle line:10%
at extremely high rate of speed.

00:51:52.690 --> 00:51:57.520 align:middle line:84%
It passed over the control
tower and then it stopped.

00:51:57.520 --> 00:51:59.680 align:middle line:90%
It was an orange-ish color.

00:51:59.680 --> 00:52:01.900 align:middle line:84%
Sort of popped into
my mind at the time

00:52:01.900 --> 00:52:04.720 align:middle line:84%
that somebody's flying
a basketball out here.

00:52:04.720 --> 00:52:08.860 align:middle line:84%
There were lights
around the center of it.

00:52:08.860 --> 00:52:12.520 align:middle line:84%
It was more like portholes, and
then you were seeing the light

00:52:12.520 --> 00:52:13.840 align:middle line:90%
from the inside.

00:52:13.840 --> 00:52:18.250 align:middle line:84%
But it hovered momentarily,
reversed its course,

00:52:18.250 --> 00:52:20.665 align:middle line:84%
and went back out at
a high rate of speed.

00:52:20.665 --> 00:52:24.190 align:middle line:90%


00:52:24.190 --> 00:52:27.940 align:middle line:10%
>> Even more alarming incidents
took place on both sides

00:52:27.940 --> 00:52:28.870 align:middle line:10%
of the Cold War.

00:52:28.870 --> 00:52:32.200 align:middle line:90%


00:52:32.200 --> 00:52:35.500 align:middle line:10%
According to one secret
Soviet documents,

00:52:35.500 --> 00:52:39.250 align:middle line:10%
a UFO hovered over a
Ukrainian nuclear base

00:52:39.250 --> 00:52:41.560 align:middle line:10%
for nearly an hour.

00:52:41.560 --> 00:52:45.220 align:middle line:84%
Inexplicably, several
missiles suddenly switched

00:52:45.220 --> 00:52:49.150 align:middle line:84%
to full combat readiness
and began a launch sequence

00:52:49.150 --> 00:52:52.690 align:middle line:84%
without any
authentication codes.

00:52:52.690 --> 00:52:56.620 align:middle line:84%
After 15 heart stopping
seconds, the countdown

00:52:56.620 --> 00:53:03.420 align:middle line:84%
to a potential Armageddon ceased
as abruptly as it had started.

00:53:03.420 --> 00:53:06.000 align:middle line:10%
>> As this object passed
over the missile site,

00:53:06.000 --> 00:53:09.330 align:middle line:10%
we will start getting erratic
indications on that missile.

00:53:09.330 --> 00:53:12.090 align:middle line:10%
The bad thing was we also
got a launch indicator.

00:53:12.090 --> 00:53:14.700 align:middle line:10%
>> Does that mean that the
launch sequence has been

00:53:14.700 --> 00:53:15.720 align:middle line:10%
triggered?

00:53:15.720 --> 00:53:19.080 align:middle line:10%
>> That means that the missile
has received a launch signal.

00:53:19.080 --> 00:53:23.640 align:middle line:84%
The countdown had to
be manually aborted.

00:53:23.640 --> 00:53:25.240 align:middle line:90%
>> We have UFOs in the area.

00:53:25.240 --> 00:53:28.530 align:middle line:84%
>> These witnesses are some of
the most highly vetted military

00:53:28.530 --> 00:53:32.040 align:middle line:84%
officers in charge of the
world's most devastating

00:53:32.040 --> 00:53:33.900 align:middle line:90%
armaments.

00:53:33.900 --> 00:53:36.390 align:middle line:84%
If what they're
reporting is accurate,

00:53:36.390 --> 00:53:39.990 align:middle line:84%
then the pattern
is hard to avoid.

00:53:39.990 --> 00:53:43.920 align:middle line:84%
UFOs have been making
incursions into top security

00:53:43.920 --> 00:53:48.800 align:middle line:84%
nuclear facilities
decade after decade.

00:53:48.800 --> 00:53:50.180 align:middle line:90%
>> To me, it's pretty clear.

00:53:50.180 --> 00:53:52.220 align:middle line:84%
This is just-- we're
shining a light on this.

00:53:52.220 --> 00:53:53.907 align:middle line:90%
We're pointing it out.

00:53:53.907 --> 00:53:55.865 align:middle line:84%
What are you people doing
with nuclear weapons?

00:53:55.865 --> 00:54:42.585 align:middle line:90%


00:54:42.585 --> 00:54:45.840 align:middle line:84%
>> As the '90s dawned
and the walls fell down,

00:54:45.840 --> 00:54:50.370 align:middle line:84%
it was as if humanity itself
was demanding to be seen as one

00:54:50.370 --> 00:54:52.890 align:middle line:90%
people and one world.

00:54:52.890 --> 00:54:55.020 align:middle line:90%
The Soviet Union had dissolved.

00:54:55.020 --> 00:55:01.050 align:middle line:84%
And history's spotlight began to
shine on long darkened corners.

00:55:01.050 --> 00:55:03.810 align:middle line:10%
>> Different officials were
looking for ways to open

00:55:03.810 --> 00:55:08.250 align:middle line:10%
dialogue with the West and
embrace all the changes that

00:55:08.250 --> 00:55:11.220 align:middle line:10%
were underway in their
country at the time.

00:55:11.220 --> 00:55:13.800 align:middle line:84%
>> This is George Knapp in
Moscow, the city many are--

00:55:13.800 --> 00:55:16.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Knapp's team was invited
to Moscow by government

00:55:16.680 --> 00:55:20.910 align:middle line:84%
and military officials who were
willing to share decades worth

00:55:20.910 --> 00:55:22.650 align:middle line:90%
of UFO files.

00:55:22.650 --> 00:55:24.390 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING RUSSIAN]

00:55:24.390 --> 00:55:27.150 align:middle line:84%
>> General Igor Maltsev,
for seven years commander

00:55:27.150 --> 00:55:29.370 align:middle line:84%
of the entire Soviet
Air Defense System,

00:55:29.370 --> 00:55:32.700 align:middle line:84%
recalls a UFO flap
over Moscow in 1990,

00:55:32.700 --> 00:55:36.000 align:middle line:84%
hundreds of visual and radar
observations by military

00:55:36.000 --> 00:55:36.840 align:middle line:90%
personnel.

00:55:36.840 --> 00:55:39.150 align:middle line:84%
Maltsev confirms
his standing order

00:55:39.150 --> 00:55:41.580 align:middle line:90%
was don't fire on the UFO.

00:55:41.580 --> 00:55:44.850 align:middle line:84%
March 1991, radar at
the Leningrad Airport

00:55:44.850 --> 00:55:48.780 align:middle line:84%
detects first one, then two,
then three unidentified objects

00:55:48.780 --> 00:55:50.460 align:middle line:90%
hovering over a nuclear plant.

00:55:50.460 --> 00:55:55.260 align:middle line:84%
From a dead stop, the UFO zipped
away at 2,000 miles per hour.

00:55:55.260 --> 00:55:57.750 align:middle line:84%
Jacques Vallee was
one of few Westerners

00:55:57.750 --> 00:56:00.360 align:middle line:84%
to personally investigate
the case by meeting

00:56:00.360 --> 00:56:01.885 align:middle line:90%
with Russian sources firsthand.

00:56:01.885 --> 00:56:05.650 align:middle line:84%
>> An object hovered near
a nuclear power plant

00:56:05.650 --> 00:56:08.300 align:middle line:84%
in [RUSSIAN] and a beam from
that object melted the asphalt

00:56:08.300 --> 00:56:09.100 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:56:09.100 --> 00:56:11.830 align:middle line:84%
>> The intention was maybe we
would be able to find out from

00:56:11.830 --> 00:56:15.760 align:middle line:84%
the Russians more about what the
American government knows about

00:56:15.760 --> 00:56:18.370 align:middle line:84%
UFOs than we will ever learn
from the American government

00:56:18.370 --> 00:56:19.210 align:middle line:90%
itself.

00:56:19.210 --> 00:56:21.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Governor, are you
ready to take the oath?

00:56:21.050 --> 00:56:21.850 align:middle line:90%
>> I am.

00:56:21.850 --> 00:56:26.190 align:middle line:10%
>> When a young, open-minded
president was sworn in, one

00:56:26.190 --> 00:56:29.700 align:middle line:10%
of America's most highly
placed civilians saw a chance

00:56:29.700 --> 00:56:33.060 align:middle line:10%
for a new government
transparency on the phenomenon.

00:56:33.060 --> 00:56:36.420 align:middle line:84%
>> As a means of access
to people to the wonders

00:56:36.420 --> 00:56:37.500 align:middle line:90%
of nature.

00:56:37.500 --> 00:56:39.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Heir to the power
and influence of one

00:56:39.780 --> 00:56:43.620 align:middle line:84%
of the world's wealthiest
families, Laurence Rockefeller,

00:56:43.620 --> 00:56:46.500 align:middle line:84%
philanthropist and
conservationist,

00:56:46.500 --> 00:56:50.400 align:middle line:84%
also had a passionate
interest in UFOs.

00:56:50.400 --> 00:56:58.260 align:middle line:10%
>> His idea was to approach
the president with a plea

00:56:58.260 --> 00:57:03.660 align:middle line:10%
for making available the
data that the government had

00:57:03.660 --> 00:57:05.190 align:middle line:10%
on the subject.

00:57:05.190 --> 00:57:09.930 align:middle line:10%
>> The first inclination
by particularly people

00:57:09.930 --> 00:57:13.170 align:middle line:10%
in government is you've
got to be kidding me.

00:57:13.170 --> 00:57:15.120 align:middle line:10%
You want me-- you
want me to risk

00:57:15.120 --> 00:57:19.170 align:middle line:10%
my career by getting
deeply into the rabbit

00:57:19.170 --> 00:57:21.390 align:middle line:10%
hole of talking about UFOs.

00:57:21.390 --> 00:57:26.530 align:middle line:84%
And so there's a
tremendous resistance.

00:57:26.530 --> 00:57:29.320 align:middle line:10%
>> Rockefeller met with
President Clinton's Science

00:57:29.320 --> 00:57:33.370 align:middle line:10%
Advisor, Jack Gibbons, at the
White House and persuaded him

00:57:33.370 --> 00:57:35.480 align:middle line:10%
to take action.

00:57:35.480 --> 00:57:37.370 align:middle line:84%
Rockefeller was
then asked to pick

00:57:37.370 --> 00:57:42.650 align:middle line:84%
a case that the White House
should attempt to declassify.

00:57:42.650 --> 00:57:47.370 align:middle line:84%
He chose the 1947
Roswell incident, noting,

00:57:47.370 --> 00:57:50.420 align:middle line:84%
quote, "Many are
convinced that Roswell

00:57:50.420 --> 00:57:55.520 align:middle line:84%
marks the beginning of
government secrecy about UFOs."

00:57:55.520 --> 00:57:59.540 align:middle line:10%
>> Jack had actually
gone to the Air Force,

00:57:59.540 --> 00:58:02.750 align:middle line:10%
asked then Secretary Widnall,
who was the Secretary

00:58:02.750 --> 00:58:07.610 align:middle line:10%
of the Air Force, to take a
look particularly at the records

00:58:07.610 --> 00:58:09.620 align:middle line:10%
around Roswell, New Mexico.

00:58:09.620 --> 00:58:13.760 align:middle line:10%
>> "Dear Colonel Cavitt, the
General Accounting Office seeks

00:58:13.760 --> 00:58:18.500 align:middle line:10%
to fully explain the claim that
the US government recovered

00:58:18.500 --> 00:58:21.230 align:middle line:10%
an alien spacecraft
near Roswell,

00:58:21.230 --> 00:58:26.840 align:middle line:10%
New Mexico in July 1947 and
since that time has covered up

00:58:26.840 --> 00:58:29.410 align:middle line:10%
that fact."

00:58:29.410 --> 00:58:31.890 align:middle line:84%
>> The Army Air Forces has
announced that a flying disk

00:58:31.890 --> 00:58:34.650 align:middle line:84%
has been found and is now in
the possession of the Army.

00:58:34.650 --> 00:58:37.610 align:middle line:90%


00:58:37.610 --> 00:58:40.940 align:middle line:10%
>> According to my dad,
there was a bad thunderstorm

00:58:40.940 --> 00:58:42.350 align:middle line:10%
the night before.

00:58:42.350 --> 00:58:45.380 align:middle line:10%
And the next day, he
was out on the ranch

00:58:45.380 --> 00:58:46.880 align:middle line:10%
and he found this debris.

00:58:46.880 --> 00:58:50.360 align:middle line:10%
>> The disk landed at a
ranch at Corona, New Mexico.

00:58:50.360 --> 00:58:53.270 align:middle line:10%
And the rancher turned
it over to the Air Force.

00:58:53.270 --> 00:58:57.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Roswell was then home to the
world's only nuclear air wing,

00:58:57.710 --> 00:59:02.030 align:middle line:84%
including the B-29 that had
dropped the first atomic bomb

00:59:02.030 --> 00:59:04.880 align:middle line:90%
on Hiroshima.

00:59:04.880 --> 00:59:09.290 align:middle line:10%
The base's Chief Intelligence
Officer, Major Jesse Marcel,

00:59:09.290 --> 00:59:14.140 align:middle line:10%
was dispatched to the
ranch to investigate.

00:59:14.140 --> 00:59:16.465 align:middle line:10%
>> We had to follow
the rancher out there.

00:59:16.465 --> 00:59:20.020 align:middle line:10%
With just verbal directions,
we never would have found it.

00:59:20.020 --> 00:59:23.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Marcel and another officer
were the first military

00:59:23.500 --> 00:59:25.660 align:middle line:90%
to arrive at the crash site.

00:59:25.660 --> 00:59:30.160 align:middle line:84%
They came upon an expanse of
unrecognizable debris strewn

00:59:30.160 --> 00:59:33.670 align:middle line:84%
across an area the size of
a dozen football fields.

00:59:33.670 --> 00:59:37.440 align:middle line:90%


00:59:37.440 --> 00:59:38.940 align:middle line:10%
>> There was so much of it.

00:59:38.940 --> 00:59:41.730 align:middle line:10%
It was scattered over
such a vast area.

00:59:41.730 --> 00:59:46.230 align:middle line:10%
We found a piece of
metal about a foot

00:59:46.230 --> 00:59:49.903 align:middle line:10%
and 1/2 to 2 feet wide and
about 2 or 3 feet long.

00:59:49.903 --> 00:59:51.570 align:middle line:10%
Felt like you had
nothing in your hands.

00:59:51.570 --> 00:59:53.880 align:middle line:10%
It wasn't any
thicker than the foil

00:59:53.880 --> 00:59:55.770 align:middle line:10%
out of a pack of cigarettes.

00:59:55.770 --> 00:59:58.350 align:middle line:84%
The thing about
it that got me is

00:59:58.350 --> 00:59:59.970 align:middle line:90%
that you couldn't even bend it.

00:59:59.970 --> 01:00:01.500 align:middle line:90%
You couldn't even dent it.

